The paper deals with the capacity of a discrete memoryless channel for bit commitment, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the security of the bit commitment protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses concepts from coding theory (cs.CC) and communication theory (cs.CE) to solve the problem. Additionally, the paper mentions extensions to quantum channels, which suggests a connection to quantum information (cs.QI).
